latestPosts.caption:
🇮🇳 Mahindra Racing back on the Formula E podium! Edoardo Mortara finished P2 at the #JakartaEPrix, narrowly missing out on victory to Cupra Kiro’s Dan Ticktum. This is the Indian team’s second podium finish this season, following Nyck de Vries’ P2 finish at Monaco.

De Vries unfortunately retired from the race, with his car in red unsafe mode. Nevertheless, Mahindra holds on to 5th place in the teams’ championship.
.
.
.

Here's the latest creation from the students of the Skoda Auto Vocational School 🚴🏽

Based on the Superb Estate, the L&K 130 is a purpose-built support car for cycle races. The project took over 2,000 working hours to complete and will be displayed at the 112th Tour de France this July. 

- Custom roof rack
- extendable rear section 
- Illuminated grille 
- A display mounted on the dashboard to monitor the race
- Unique sliding door 
- Comes with a radio transmitter and a beverage cooler

The Honda City gets a new limited-run Sport variant🌶️
Launched at Rs 14.89 lakh, the mid-spec variant costs Rs 49,000 more than the V CVT variant, and it gets a host of cosmetic changes inside and outside. 

- 1.5-litre NA petrol engine 
- 121hp
- 7-step CVT 
- Ambient light 
- Leatherette upholstery 
- ADAS Suite 
- 8-inch infotainment screen 
- Blacked out treatment for the grille, spoiler and alloys 
- Red and black interior trim
